headline: Why Shares in Synopsys Popped Higher Today
summary: It's far from clear whether there will be any direct benefit to Synopsys from the latest agreement.  Shares in electronic design automation (EDA) company Synopsys (NASDAQ: SNPS) were up by more than 5% at 10 a.m. ET today.  The positive developments came after officials from China and the U.S. confirmed that a new trade framework had been agreed upon between the two countries.
